name: Update sessions and resolve conflicting cached credentials
body:
## What's Changed
* Quick Typo fix by @markliederbach in https://github.com/easysnmp/easysnmp/pull/77
* Don't hardcode gcc compiler flags by @sthomen in https://github.com/easysnmp/easysnmp/pull/52
* edit readme  by @cybersol795 in https://github.com/easysnmp/easysnmp/pull/101
* Move CI/CD pipeline from Travis CI to Github Actions by @kamakazikamikaze in https://github.com/easysnmp/easysnmp/pull/137
* Allow manual dispatch of GA events by @kamakazikamikaze in https://github.com/easysnmp/easysnmp/pull/138
* Fix raising of EasySNMPTimeoutError by @uedvt359 in https://github.com/easysnmp/easysnmp/pull/130
* Memory leak patches by @kamakazikamikaze in https://github.com/easysnmp/easysnmp/pull/142
* fix compilation for configurable privacy/authentication algorithms by @uedvt359 in https://github.com/easysnmp/easysnmp/pull/143
* Creation of Interface.h by @carlkid1499 in https://github.com/easysnmp/easysnmp/pull/145
* Create issue templates by @kamakazikamikaze in https://github.com/easysnmp/easysnmp/pull/150
* Only run test checks if source code or package build files are changed by @kamakazikamikaze in https://github.com/easysnmp/easysnmp/pull/151
* Code formatting formalized, CI/CD adjustments, and templated issues by @kamakazikamikaze in https://github.com/easysnmp/easysnmp/pull/152
* Clear user from Net-SNMP cache when closing session capsule by @kamakazikamikaze in https://github.com/easysnmp/easysnmp/pull/157
* Bump release to 0.2.6 by @kamakazikamikaze in https://github.com/easysnmp/easysnmp/pull/159
* Publish 0.2.6 by @kamakazikamikaze in https://github.com/easysnmp/easysnmp/pull/160

## New Contributors
* @markliederbach made their first contribution in https://github.com/easysnmp/easysnmp/pull/77
* @sthomen made their first contribution in https://github.com/easysnmp/easysnmp/pull/52
* @cybersol795 made their first contribution in https://github.com/easysnmp/easysnmp/pull/101
* @carlkid1499 made their first contribution in https://github.com/easysnmp/easysnmp/pull/145

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/easysnmp/easysnmp/compare/0.2.5...0.2.6

name: 0.2.6a: Memory leak fixes and Python exception handling
body: This is an early release to prioritize users experiencing exception and memory leak issues. This is deemed stable for use despite being marked as pre-release. A full release with additional fixes and documentation updates will come in the future.
